	<h2>Travel Thrifty</h2>
	<table>
		<tr>
		<th>Plan Ahead</th>
		<td>
	 	  <ul>
		    <li>Save money by making reservations ahead of time.</li> 
				<li>Save time on vacation by making an itinerary of what you want to do.</li>
				<li>Traveling is cheaper right after the holidays and New Years'.</li>
				<li>Tuesdays are the cheapest days to fly!</li>
		  </ul>
		</td>	
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<th>Be Flexible</th>
			<td>
			  <ul>
				  <li>Fly into a less popular airport in a city near your destination for a cheaper flight.</li>
					<li>Catching a red-eye flight can save money if you're up for it!</li>
					<li>Do not live by the itinerary. You may find hiden gems in the area.</li>
					<li>Plan downtime, vacations are supposed to be relaxing!</li>
			  </ul>
	  </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<th>Money&amp;Time Saving Apps</th>
			<td>
		    <ul>
	        <li>Hopper will track the flights and prices you're interested in, and show what months are cheaper to fly.</li>
	        <li>Tripadvisor is a lot of information on local attractions along with reviews.</li>
          <li>Alltrails is like Tripadvisor but for hiking trails! We recommend looking at recent reviews to see if the trials are still in good condition.</li>
        </ul>
			</td>	
		</tr>
